    {
      "id": "1b44750c-f3ba-80b3-a488-fe49e1d8d1e3",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The groups formed algorithmically were shown to perform better than random grouping. Moreover, the peer satisfaction  and self-perception were higher for students in the homogenous groups for the idea exchange tasks. In the reading tasks, there were no significant differences. ",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
